---
import T7Layout from '../layouts/T7Layout.astro';
import MidPageCta from '../components/MidPageCta.astro';
import ContactForm from '../components/ContactForm.astro';
import { breadcrumbSchema } from '../lib/schema';

const title = 'Fees';
const description =
  'How UK Mortgages Worldwide charges for advice and arrangement. Most clients pay no fee. Up to £1,100 may apply in specific circumstances.';

const schemas = [
  breadcrumbSchema([
    { name: 'Home', path: '/' },
    { name: 'Fees' },
  ]),
];
---

<T7Layout
  title={title}
  description={description}
  h1="Fees"
  eyebrow="LEGAL"
  schemas={schemas}
>
  <p>
    UK Mortgages Worldwide is operated by Mortgage One. Most clients pay
    no fee for our advice and arrangement service.
  </p>

  <h2>When fees apply</h2>
  <p>
    A fee of up to £1,100 may be charged for advice in relation to mortgage
    and protection services. In most cases, this fee is waived. A fee may
    become payable where a formal mortgage offer has been secured, and you
    then choose not to proceed (for example, if you decide to instruct
    another broker after we have completed the work).
  </p>
  <p>
    Full details of any applicable fees are set out in our Initial
    Disclosure Document and your Authority to Proceed, which we will
    provide and explain before any chargeable activity takes place.
  </p>

  <h2>Lender procuration fees</h2>
  <p>
    In most cases our remuneration comes from a procuration fee paid by
    the lender on completion of your mortgage. This is disclosed to you
    before you commit to any product.
  </p>

  <h2>Other costs</h2>
  <p>
    Additional costs, charges, or taxes relating to your mortgage or
    protection arrangements may apply. These are not charged by or payable
    through UK Mortgages Worldwide. Examples include lender arrangement
    fees, valuation fees, legal fees, and stamp duty.
  </p>

  <h2>Initial Disclosure Document</h2>
  <p>
    We provide a written Initial Disclosure Document at the start of any
    engagement. It sets out the services we provide, how we charge, and
    our regulatory status. Send an enquiry and we will provide it before
    any work begins.
  </p>

  <MidPageCta variant="hero" />

  <ContactForm />
</T7Layout>
